g.text: - Fully managed auth backend (Supabase handles users, tokens)
- Uses JWT tokens; works well with Server Components and App Router
✅ Ideal if you're already using Supabase (which you are)
- Store login info in localStorage or cookie
- Good for: quick demos, learning, non-secure apps
- Built for Next.js (supports App Router with experimental setup)
🟣 4. Auth0 / Clerk / Firebase Auth / Magic Links
- Offer pre-built UI, biometric login, multi-factor auth
- Built using next-auth, jsonwebtoken, bcrypt, etc.
- Best for full control (e.g., enterprise apps)
